description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI Austria IMI 25/50 Index.
 The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities in the index. The index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index with a capping methodology applied to issuer weights so that no single issuer of a component exceeds 25% of the index weight, and all issuers with a weight above 5% do not cumulatively exceed 50% of the index weight. The fund is non-diversified.
